'''Malcolm Watson Dixon''' (1934<ref name="GRO Birth" /> &ndash; [[April 9]], [[2020]])<ref name="Death" /> was an actor who played an [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] warrior in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']]. Stock footage of his Ewok character from the film was later used in the video game ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront]]''.

He later worked with [[George Lucas]] on the [[1988]] film [[Willow (film)|''Willow'']], in which he played a Nelwyn band member.

Dixon also appeared in [[Wikipedia:Willy Wonka & The Chocolate Factory|''Willy Wonka & The Chocolate Factory'']] as an Oompa Loompa.

